{
  "texts": [
    "Implicitly, this type of condition can also be seen in the aforementioned work of Arroyo-Rabasa and Bouchitté [5] and Bate et al [8].",
    "It should be stated that these different groups (including the present author) realized these types of connections to PDEs independently as is also indicated in a recent survey by Marchese [31].",
    "The main problem is that in most cases the PDE type conditions are actually known to fail when considering pointwise estimates.",
    "One contribution of the present paper is in showing the necesssity of a pointwise PDE type condition for a Flat Chain Conjecture, even if one must consider the conjecture without the finite mass condition.On the other hand, the results of Marchese and Merlo [32] and De Masi and Marchese [19] provide a plausible sufficient PDE type condition for FCC(AK) [k, d].",
    "The main point is that they do not require finding a Lipschitz map solving the underlying PDE in a pointwise sense, but instead only in a very weak measure-theoretic sense.Finally, it should be stated that in all cases in which we disprove FCC(L)[k, d] we actually produce a metric k-current with compact support but infinite flat norm."
  ]
}